<font color="#FF0000">HOW TO JERK MY CHAIN</font><br>
<tt>Thu Oct 30 20:16:27 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Old SW is just being moved by all the stimuli in the stories I have been reading.  Some really solid items to digest.<br><br>
Cook I like your Black and White piece.  A real image-maker.  I can see the whole thing playing.  It doesn't take much to know you are talking from your gut and feel every word.  Like a good poet, no emotion, no poetry.<br><br>
No problem about the little clip, use it as you please.  Just remind Jerry that indecision is the key to flexibility.<br><br>
Stimuli.  I still can't listen to a good bugler play taps without flashing back to friends grave site with the bugler playing, the rain falling, and the honor guard firing over the grave.  This isn't a short clip.  It begins a review of episodes.<br><br>
When I see the flag and hear the National Anthem I get chills and swell up with pride (An easy drift and good thoughts).  When I look around and see the disrespect others are paying it really pisses me off and I have to bite my tongue because they don't feel as I do.<br><br>
When a group gets together and begin to put down the soldier or mock the uniform I get vocal.  Almost got fired one day when I told my boss if he couldn't respect the men he had made his living from then shut up in my presence.  I have no tolerance.  As such I feel the same way about any servant who wears his uniform with pride.<br><br>
Just a few, but more to come.  My strongest is still Taps.  Beautiful.<br>

<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


